56:05.400 --> 56:07.926
Once upon a time, somewhere
miles and miles beneath the

56:08.040 --> 56:11.567
surface of the ocean,
there lived a young

56:11.720 --> 56:13.802
octopus named Nina.

56:13.920 --> 56:18.130
Nina spent most of her time
alone making strange creations

56:18.240 --> 56:22.645
out of rocks and shells.
And she was very happy.

56:22.760 --> 56:26.731
But then on Monday the
shark showed up.

56:26.840 --> 56:29.650
"What's your name?"
said the shark.

56:29.760 --> 56:31.000
"Nina," she replied.

56:31.120 --> 56:34.886
"Do you want to be my friend?"
he asked.

56:35.000 --> 56:35.523
"OK.

56:35.600 --> 56:38.649
What do I have to
do?" said Nina.

56:38.760 --> 56:40.091
"Not much,"
said the shark.

56:40.200 --> 56:43.727
"Just let me eat one
of your arms."

56:43.840 --> 56:46.923
Nina had never had a friend
before, so she wondered if

56:47.040 --> 56:49.725
this was what you had
to do to get one.

56:49.880 --> 56:53.441
She looked down at her eight
arms and decided it wouldn't

56:53.560 --> 56:54.686
be so bad to give up one.

56:54.800 --> 56:59.442
So she donated an arm to her
wonderful new friend.

57:02.160 --> 57:02.683
Wow.

57:02.800 --> 57:05.565
Every day that week, Nina and
the shark would play together.

57:05.680 --> 57:10.049
They explored caves, built
castles of sand, and swam

57:10.160 --> 57:11.605
really, really fast.

57:11.720 --> 57:14.929
And every night the shark would
be hungry, and Nina

57:15.040 --> 57:18.681
would give him another one
of her arms to eat.

57:20.800 --> 57:26.648
On Sunday, after playing all
day, the shark told Nina that

57:26.760 --> 57:28.524
he was very hungry.

57:28.640 --> 57:30.005
"I don't understand,"
she said.

57:30.120 --> 57:33.310
"I've already given you six of
my arms, and now you want one more?"

57:33.420 --> 57:37.728
The shark looked at her
with a friendly smile and

57:37.840 --> 57:39.763
said, "I don't want one.

57:39.880 --> 57:46.570
This time I want them all."
"But why?" Nina asked.

57:46.680 --> 57:51.568
And the shark replied, "because
that's what friends are for."

57:54.680 --> 57:59.322
When the shark finished
his meal, he felt

57:59.440 --> 58:00.885
very sad and lonely.

58:01.000 --> 58:05.085
He missed having someone to
explore caves, build castles,

58:05.200 --> 58:08.522
and swim really, really
fast with.

58:10.680 --> 58:14.890
He missed Nina very much.

58:15.000 --> 58:19.366
So he-- he swam away to
find another friend.

58:32.760 --> 58:35.411
Jayden?

58:37.680 --> 58:40.411
Did your dad ever hurt you?

58:49.160 --> 58:51.561
Does he still hurt you?

59:30.800 --> 59:34.361
We can't let her
go back there.

59:38.920 --> 59:41.571
That's not going to happen.

59:45.920 --> 59:49.720
You were pretty amazing today.

59:49.840 --> 59:50.841
Thank you.

01:00:29.360 --> 01:00:30.964
Hmm?

01:00:34.560 --> 01:00:35.925
More, please.

01:00:36.040 --> 01:00:37.728
More for everyone.
More of everything.

01:00:37.840 --> 01:00:39.842
Anyone, dessert first?

01:00:39.960 --> 01:00:43.131
